  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n\n## 2026-04-29 05:03 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC lost clean bearish whale consensus, but ETH / SOL / HYPE stayed decisively short\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh Pillar 1 copy-intel pass, quantify the current HL leaderboard by notional instead of just headcount, and decide whether the new PM mixed bullish print is strong enough to challenge the whale book.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Fresh HL scan came in **BTC 4L/5S, ETH 3L/5S, SOL 3L/5S**, but the important shift was inside BTC, not the counts alone.\n- `anon-0xfc66` flipped **BTC SHORT -> LONG** and is now long about **$4.31M BTC** while keeping large shorts in **ETH ($7.25M)**, **SOL ($5.37M)**, and **HYPE ($6.96M)**.\n- `anon-0x8fcc` flipped back to **BTC SHORT ($4.96M)** and `anon-0x3bca` opened a fresh **BTC SHORT ($4.40M)**, so BTC is now a split whale battleground instead of a clean one-way short.\n- Notional-weighted leaderboard state is:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$20.39M** vs shorts **$12.33M** \u2192 net **+$8.06M long** despite bearish headcount\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.14M** vs shorts **$34.67M** \u2192 overwhelming short consensus\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.20M** vs shorts **$13.03M** \u2192 overwhelming short consensus\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.41M** vs shorts **$11.90M** \u2192 strong short consensus\n- Current PM copy state is only **bullish / 20 confidence / mixed** with high-price flow (`avg_signal_price 0.982`) and moderate funded size (**$692**), which is too weak and noisy to overrule the HL whale posture.\n- I wrote the detailed artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/copy-intel-rescan-2026-04-29-0503.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The real change is not a broad risk-on turn. It is a relative-value rotation where BTC lost its clean bearish alignment because the biggest wallet stayed massively long BTC while other whales reloaded shorts. Meanwhile ETH, SOL, and HYPE remain decisively short by size, not just by trader count. That makes BTC lower-trust directionally, but it does not weaken the broader copy-intel bear case in the weaker beta names.\n\n**Decision:** Keep **ETH short** as the strongest copy-intel signal, keep **SOL short** and **HYPE short** as strong secondaries, and downgrade **BTC** to **split / tactical only** instead of treating it as clean bearish consensus. Do **not** let the current PM mixed bullish print overrule the HL whale book.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, test whether PM smart-entry should explicitly haircut bullish copy influence whenever HL notional consensus is net long BTC but still overwhelmingly short ETH/SOL/HYPE, so the bot stops flattening this relative-value split into one generic market-wide copy read.\n\n## 2026-04-29 01:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fear & Greed only earns a small fear-side boost; the greed penalty is unproven and should come out\n\n**Task:** Re-test the Fear & Greed overlay against the full `data/03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` sample, check whether it still improves PM",
